arf_vad — standalone extraction of the adaptive SNR voice activity
detector from the arf-recog-adaptive-vad UniMRCP plugin, specifically:

  plugins/arf-recog-adaptive-vad/src/arf_vad.c
  plugins/arf-recog-adaptive-vad/src/arf_vad.h

The detection algorithm is unchanged (adaptive noise floor with an
asymmetric one-pole tracker, SNR onset/offset gates with hysteresis and
leaky integrators, DC blocker, zero-crossing fricative assist, proximity
gates). See arf_vad.h for the list of mechanical modifications
(allocation, types, frame API, logging) made to remove the APR/APT/MPF
dependencies.

The spectral (libfvad) vote fusion is retained in the API but unused
here: without a caller supplying votes the detector runs energy/SNR-only.
